# TypeScript Learning Journey

I started learning TypeScript to improve how I write JavaScript. This repository is where I keep track of what I'm learning — small practice files, notes, and experiments while working through the fundamentals.

This isn't meant to be a polished project. It's simply a place where I document my learning and practice consistently.

---

## Why TypeScript?

While building JavaScript projects, I often ran into bugs caused by simple mistakes that could have been caught earlier. TypeScript helps by adding types and better tooling, which makes code easier to understand and maintain.

I'm learning it so I can write more reliable code and use it in my future React projects.

---

